  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, a rapid change in gaze direction from one screen location to another could be executed by an eye movement, or a combined eye and head movement (see Fig. 1), without the eye tracker's gaze output allowing to tell the difference between the two.",
    "While the former can be referred to as a saccade, the latter has been described as a gaze shift or gaze saccade (cf.",
    "Freedman, 2008; Hooge, Niehorster, Nyström, & Hessels, 2024a).",
    "This distinction may seem small, but may be critical when reporting and communicating results about oculomotor behavior.",
    "Consequently, a more appropriate name for a 'remote eye tracker' would be a 'remote gaze tracker' (Hooge et al., 2024a)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Freedman, 2008; Hooge, Niehorster, Nyström, & Hessels, 2024a).",
